Instruction: Can you describe the underlying process of the Sepsis event log?

The discovered process model begins with patients entering through ER Registration, proceeding to ER Triage, and advancing to ER Sepsis Triage. Following this, diagnostic tests (Leucocytes, CRP, LacticAcid) are frequently done in parallel (e.g., Leucocytes ↔ CRP) to monitor conditions. After testing, patients typically receive IV Liquid and IV Antibiotics, which often lead to Admission NC or to Admission IC in some cases . Post-admission NC, patients may undergo repeated testing (e.g., Admission NC → Leucocytes/CRP) or be discharged via Release A (common) or other release types (B, C, D, E), with Return ER sometimes occurring after release.
